description:
&lt;p&gt;This is a reconfigured post to enable Speech &amp; Language Therapy to develop further the rehabilitation model across the rehab pathways within Cardiff &amp; Vale UHB. The postholder will work along the stroke rehab pathway and will also work closely with the SLT Clinical Service Lead for Neuropsychiatry and Brain Injury to ensure SLT contribution to the implementation of national and local service improvement within stroke and specialist neurorehabilitation pathways. The postholder will provide clinical leadership and have delegated responsibility for performance and delivery of key service objectives. The adult SLT service is a small but dynamic service , with a robust supervision and support structure. The postholder would be part of the senior management team for the SLT service .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 19/11/2020 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Nia Came&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Senior Lead for Adult SLT&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: nia.came@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 02920743012 &lt;/p&gt;
